section.def:
Dean
                (座堂主任牧師) means the clergyman in charge of Saint
            John’s Cathedral and holding the Bishop’s licence to such office;

incumbent
                (駐堂聖品人) means a clergyman with a cure of souls in
            charge of a church and holding the Bishop’s licence thereto;

paragraph.content:
the trustees shall not be deemed personally liable for any payments
                            of money in excess of that provided or available for the purposes of the
                            church;

the election and tenure of office of an auditor and the appointment and
                    tenure of office of a treasurer and secretary and the mode of filling up casual
                    vacancies among such officers;
